dcterms:title: "And darkness was upon the face of the deep"
"And there was light"
"And God said, Let there be light"
"And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters"
"And God called the dry land Earth"
"And God said, Let there be lights in the firmament of heaven"
"And God said, Let the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures"
"So God created man in his own image"
"The creation of the world"
"We were Pharaoh's slaves in Egypt"
"And the Egyptians pursued, and went in after them into the midst of the sea, all Pharaoh's horses, his chariots, and his horsemen"
"Let my people go"
"And they made their lives bitter with hard service, in mortar and in brick"
"And the Lord brought us out of Egypt"
"And she told him the same story, saying, "The Hebrew servant, whom you have brought among us, came in to me to laugh at me"
"And behold, seven ears of grain, plump and good, were growing on one stalk"
"And behold, after them sprouted seven ears, thin and wblighted by the east wind"
"And let them gather all the food ... under the authority of Pharaoh"
"We were Pharaoh's slaves in Egypt"
"She took pity on him and said, This is one of the Hebrews' children"
"She named him Moses, "Because," she said, "I drew him out of the water"
"And Aaron cast down his rod before Pharaoh, and it became a serpent"
"And the bush was not consumed"
"And it came to pass, when Moses held up his hand, that Israel prevailed; and when he let down his hand, Amalek prevailed"
"Then came Amalek, and fought with Israel in Rephidim"
"The bush burned with fire, and the bush was not consumed"
"And the waters were a wall unto them on their right hand, and on their left"
"And the flood was forty days upon the earth; and the waters increased, and bare up the ark, and it was lifted up above the earth"
"And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights"
"I do set my bow in the cloud"
"Make yourself an ark of gopher wood. Make rooms in the ark, and cover it inside and out with pitch"
"Two by two they came"
"And God remembered Noah, and all the beasts"
"Two by two they came"
"And the dove came back to him in the evening, and behold, in her mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf"
"I do set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between me and the earth"
"And the dove came in to him in the evening; and, lo, in her mouth was an olive leaf pluckt off"
"And the ark rested... upon the mountains of Ararat"
"I do set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between me and the earth"
"And the ark rested in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, upon the mountains of Ararat"
